Inventory Data (99% Service Level, ~99% Accuracy)

| Category    | Avg Daily Demand | Std Dev | Lead Time (days) | Z (Service Level) | Safety Stock | Reorder Point |
| ----------- | ---------------- | ------- | ---------------- | ----------------- | ------------ | ------------- |
| Beauty      | 3.78             | 2.40    | 7                | 2.326             | 14.77        | 41.23         |
| Clothing    | 3.85             | 2.46    | 7                | 2.326             | 15.15        | 42.12         |
| Electronics | 3.877            | 2.53    | 7                | 2.326             | 15.60        | 42.73         |

Summary of Inventory Data

Demand is similar across Beauty, Clothing, and Electronics, around 3.8 units/day.
Electronics demand is slightly more variable, requiring a bit more safety stock than the other categories.
Safety stock increases with service level:
At 95% service level → 10–11 units
At 99% service level → 15–16 units
Reorder points rise with safety stock to ensure stock availability during lead time.
Overall, higher service levels provide better protection against stockouts, but require more inventory.
This data helps balance product availability with inventory efficiency.
